# Privacy Policy for FreshTrack

**Last Updated:** January 01, 2026

## Introduction

Welcome to FreshTrack! We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring transparency about how we handle your data. This Privacy Policy explains our practices regarding data collection, usage, and protection.

## Developer Information

**App Name:** FreshTrack  
**Developer:** Balaji Thukuntala
**Contact Email:** balajithukuntala@gmail.com 
**Effective Date:** January 01, 2026

## Overview

FreshTrack is an offline-first mobile application designed to help users track product expiry dates and reduce food waste. We prioritize your privacy by storing all data locally on your device.

## Data Collection and Storage

### What Data We Collect

FreshTrack collects and stores the following information **locally on your device only**:

1. **Product Information:**
   - Product names
   - Expiry dates
   - Categories (Food, Medicines, Cosmetics, Beverages, Others)
   - Quantities
   - Optional notes
   - Optional barcode numbers
   - Product status (active, consumed, discarded)

2. **App Preferences:**
   - Notification settings
   - Theme preferences
   - Onboarding completion status
   - Notification advance notice days

3. **Device Permissions:**
   - **Notifications** - To send expiry reminders (Android 13+)
   - **Camera** - To scan product barcodes (optional, if implemented)

### How Data is Stored

- **All data is stored locally** on your device using Android's Room Database
- **No data is transmitted** to any external servers
- **No cloud backup** in Phase 1 (offline-only)
- **No user accounts** or authentication required
- **No personal information** collected (name, email, phone, location)

## Data Usage

### How We Use Your Data

Your data is used solely for the following purposes:

1. **Core Functionality:**
   - Display your tracked products
   - Calculate expiry dates and remaining days
   - Send local notifications for expiring products
   - Organize products by categories
   - Track product consumption and disposal

2. **App Experience:**
   - Remember your preferences (theme, notification settings)
   - Skip onboarding on subsequent app launches
   - Provide personalized expiry alerts

### How We DO NOT Use Your Data

- ❌ We do NOT share your data with third parties
- ❌ We do NOT sell your data
- ❌ We do NOT use your data for advertising
- ❌ We do NOT track your location
- ❌ We do NOT collect analytics or usage data
- ❌ We do NOT require registration or login

## Data Sharing and Third Parties

**We do not share any of your data with third parties.**

FreshTrack is a completely offline application. Your product data never leaves your device.

### Third-Party Services

Currently, FreshTrack does not integrate with any third-party services, analytics platforms, or advertising networks.

**Note:** Future versions (Phase 2) may include optional cloud backup and sync features. If implemented, we will update this Privacy Policy and request your explicit consent before enabling any data transmission features.

## Data Security

### How We Protect Your Data

1. **Local Storage:** All data is stored securely in Android's internal storage, accessible only by the FreshTrack app
2. **No Network Transmission:** Data never leaves your device
3. **Android Security:** Protected by Android's app sandboxing and permission system
4. **No External Access:** No backend servers or databases that could be compromised

### Your Responsibility

- Keep your device secure with a lock screen
- Be cautious when granting device access to others
- Regularly backup your data (export feature available)

## Your Rights and Choices

### You Have Full Control

1. **Access Your Data:** All your data is visible within the app
2. **Edit Your Data:** Modify any product information at any time
3. **Delete Your Data:** 
   - Delete individual products within the app
   - Delete all data by uninstalling the app
   - Clear app data from Android Settings
4. **Export Your Data:** Use the export feature to create a backup (CSV format)
5. **Control Notifications:** Enable/disable notifications in Settings
6. **Manage Permissions:** Revoke permissions anytime in Android Settings

### Data Retention

- Data is retained indefinitely on your device until you delete it
- Uninstalling the app permanently deletes all local data
- No data is retained on any servers (none exist)

## Children's Privacy

FreshTrack does not knowingly collect information from children under 13. The app is designed for general audiences and does not contain age-inappropriate content. Parents and guardians are responsible for supervising their children's use of the app.

## Permissions Explained

### Why We Request Permissions

1. **Notifications (Android 13+):**
   - **Why:** To send you timely alerts before products expire
   - **When:** Requested on first app launch
   - **Optional:** You can deny and manually check the app
   - **Control:** Enable/disable in Android Settings → Apps → FreshTrack → Notifications

2. **Camera (if barcode scanning is enabled):**
   - **Why:** To scan product barcodes
   - **When:** Only when you tap the scan button
   - **Optional:** You can manually enter barcode numbers
   - **Control:** Revoke in Android Settings → Apps → FreshTrack → Permissions

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do:

- The "Last Updated" date will be revised
- Significant changes will be communicated via in-app notification
- Continued use of the app constitutes acceptance of changes
- You can always review the current policy in Settings → Privacy Policy

## Future Features (Phase 2)

**Planned features that may affect privacy:**

1. **Cloud Backup & Sync** (Optional):
   - If implemented, data will be encrypted and synced to secure cloud storage
   - Will require user account creation
   - Explicit opt-in required
   - This Privacy Policy will be updated accordingly

2. **User Authentication:**
   - Email/password for cloud features
   - No data will be shared without explicit consent

3. **Analytics** (Optional):
   - Anonymized usage statistics to improve the app
   - Opt-in only, never mandatory
   - No personal information collected

**We will notify you and request permission before implementing any feature that transmits data.**

## Data Portability

You can export your data at any time:

1. Open FreshTrack
2. Go to Settings → Data & Storage → Export Data
3. Choose CSV format
4. Share via email, WhatsApp, Google Drive, etc.

This exported file contains all your product information and can be viewed in Excel, Google Sheets, or any CSV-compatible application.

## Contact Us

If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your data:

**Email:** balajithukuntala@gmail.com  
**Response Time:** Within 48 hours

You can also provide feedback within the app: Settings → Send Feedback

## Legal Compliance

This app complies with:

- Google Play Store policies
- Android platform guidelines
- General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) principles
- California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) principles

## Your Consent

By using FreshTrack, you consent to this Privacy Policy.

If you do not agree with this policy, please do not use the app.

